<br>
====<br>
Having “hide” already at level 2 (wood elf) I wish to create  an “Evade” macro such as <br>
<br>
/attack off<br>
/do ability 1 [hide in ability slot 1]<br>
/attack on<br>
<br>
Q1. &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Is it necessary to have “attack off” to hide/evade ?<br>
Q2&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp   Is it useful to use an “Evade hotkey” while Solo ?<br>
Q3. &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I understand the usefulness of evading while grouping with a real tank such as a warrior, for instance, but I am not sure that casters will like me if I do so while I am alone with them. When do you evade ?<br>
<br>
Additional issues (if you are nice and patient with me)<br>
============<br>
Q4. &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp How do you cancel or remove players from the /ignore list (my mistake)<br>
Q5. &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp What is the meaning of those  ..% … ….  …% figures in the right corner of the “environment screen”<br>
Q6. &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Can I delete a character and recreate it keeping the same name ?<br>
Q7. &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Is it normal as a wood elf to be blind at night when I leave the surroundings of a fire (only seeing the heat of NPCs in the dark) I sought that our Infravision would be better. <br>
<br>
To make you laugh and understand my pain, here is my story :<br>
================================================<br>
Last Friday, I started as a wood elf lady rogue in Kelethin . (I had been unable to go through the EQ tutorial due to system errors on my PC) <br>
<br>
So for a couple of hours, I did  exactly everything I had promised myself NOT to do from reading your board, such as being hungry and forgetting that a real nice lady had given me two plats for this purpose, not finding the lift to go down, getting lost, forgetting about quests and selling my quest items, falling from the platform at night and dying, hunting Orc Pawn at level 2 – and dying again because I forgot that my skin like …shield was gone, grouping and loosing my leader in the dark, right from the begin, putting players on /ignore by error, etc.<br>
<br>
I invented some new stupid things too, such as walking through Greater Faydark fully buffed and SOWed by another nice Druid, to discover later that I had been using “walk” instead of “run” for the last four hours, etc. In addition, Sow was at night, so I was just unable to see anything in the dark. But I decided to hunt anyway to show her how thankful and courageous I was (LOL).  <br>
<br>
I think you can see the pattern here at this point. Just too many things to handle at once.<br>
<br>
Encouragements to persevere will be welcomed  <br>
<br>
Silmarine<br>
Rogue lady of the 2d season <br>
Really frighten in the dark but attacking Orc pawns anyway.<br>
Karana Server<br>
