<br>
1) Read the Library<br>
2) Read and re-read the FAQ in Training Studio (Most people forget what it stands for, it seems <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
3) Look over the threads from the last 2-3 pages of applicable forums before posting.<br>
4) Ask away.<br>
<br>
<br>
Q1--Attack must be off to Evade<br>
Q2--Evading while soloing is pointless -- you can't drop lower on a hatelist of 1<br>
Q3--If you are the sole melee, not much point in evading onto the casters usually (though if one is overnuking, I might let them get slapped a bit)<br>
Q4--Ignored people come off the same way they go on.   (/ignore Duufus)<br>
Q5--They have to do with pings-pongs-and-packetloss.  Since they're pretty much out of my control, I only pay it attention when it starts to turn red.<br>
Q6--Sometimes.  Names get filtered past GMs.  If the first one was approved because there was no GM online, it might not make a second try. (ie)<br>
